<subSubSection id="C358655E860C6B2AFECF8B32FC91F746" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860C6B2AFECF8B32FC91F746" blockId="30.[231,1216,1862,2269]" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">Description. Shell minute, slender, high-spired turriculate anomphalous. Protoconch of ll1z smooth whorls with deviated spire, the transition from protoconch to teleoconch indistinct orthocline. Teleoconch of about 8 convex whorls with early whorls smooth and later whorls ornamented with 6 evenly spaced spiral cords; whorl profile more or less symmetrically rounded; suture deep, well impressed. Aperture oval, columellar lip slightly arcuate; base rounded.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
