<subSubSection id="C358655E860C6B2AFECC8718FD2BF45B" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860C6B2AFECC8718FD2BF45B" blockId="30.[229,1219,2508,3192]" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">
Etymology. Derived from the Latin 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860C6B2AFC288718FB25F409" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[1008,1215,2924,2962]" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptacididae" genus="Donaldina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minutissima">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860C6B2AFC288718FB25F409" box="[1008,1215,2924,2962]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">minutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
meaning extremely small.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E860C6B2AFECC87BCFA51FD84" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5860C6B2AFECC87BCFA51FD84" blockId="30.[229,1219,2508,3192]" lastBlockId="30.[1289,2264,412,543]" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">
Remarks. Six specimens recovered for this study are sufficiently well preserved to justify basing a new species. This new species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860C6B2AFC4A8050FEB1F3E3" authority="Yoo" authorityName="Yoo" class="Gastropoda" family="Streptacididae" genus="Donaldina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="filosa">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860C6B2AFC4A8050FB25F3D1" box="[914,1215,3108,3146]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">Donaldina filosa</emphasis>
Yoo
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56860C6B2AFE578025FC05F3E3" authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[399,927,3153,3192]" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Pseudoaclisina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="microspirulata" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7860C6B2AFE578025FC05F3E3" box="[399,927,3153,3192]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="93">Pseudoaclisina microspirulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20557BC860C6B2AFC6C8025FB9BF3E3" box="[948,1025,3153,3192]" pageId="30" pageNumber="93" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having a minute, slender and tall shell with fine spiral ornament, but it differs in having a more highly deviated protoconch.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
